description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM POST TO COVER MATERNITY LEAVE UNTIL 31ST MARCH 2022&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INTENSIVE CARE EXPERIENCE WOULD BE BENEFICIAL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to appoint a motivated and well organised individual with a passion for research and a keen interest in developing and supporting collaborative commercial and non commercial research within the University Health Board. The post holder will be an experienced registered nurse with a track record of involvement in research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working as part of a well established team, the post holder will be involved in ensuring that any research undertaken within the University Health Board safeguards the well being of the research participants, to include patients, staff and control subjects. This will involve supporting participants through the research pathway, in accordance with the research protocol and relevant legislation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will support the Assistant Director for R&amp;D and the R&amp;D Manager in meeting the Research and Development Division, Welsh Government Key Performance Indicators and Metrics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 17th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa Roche&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Senior Research Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa.Roche2@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
